First Edition.

30cm x 22cm. 304 pages, colour photographs, 1 DVD. Black cloth, gilt lettering, pictorial jacket.

The history of one of Australia’s oldest rugby league club’s from 1933 to 2008. More than 300 photographs and lists every A-Grade player. Includes the DVD containing interviews with Cameron Smith, Bill Pearson and club greats, eight grand finals, and Rupert McCalls famous poem The Ghosts of Bishop Park. This is the limited hardback edition.

. Fine Condition.
